Enum Dice

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<Dice>
com.algonquincollege.cst8284.assignment2.util.Dice
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Dice>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum Dice
extends java.lang.Enum<Dice>
the enum Dice contains 7 and only 7 instances, every instance representing a dice: For example, FOUR means a dice with 4 sides from 1-4, SIX means a dice with 6 sides from 1-6, and so on.
